<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="230" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,319,558]" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,235,319,341]" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">Diagnosis</emphasis>
:—The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hilliard 1977)" baseAuthorityName="Hilliard" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[550,806,320,342]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Gerbera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kraussii">
<emphasis box="[550,655,320,341]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">G. kraussii</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hilliard, O. M." box="[667,798,320,342]" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" refId="ref3050" refString="Hilliard, O. M. (1977) Compositae in Natal. University of Natal Press, Pietermaritzburg, 659 pp." type="book" year="1977">Hilliard 1977</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in its upper leaf surface being pilose rather than velvety pubescent, in its leaf base never contracting into a winged petiole, and in its pappus that is whitish rather than violet-purple. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hilliard 1977)" baseAuthorityName="Hilliard" baseAuthorityYear="1977" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Gerbera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ambigua">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="230">G. ambigua</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hilliard, O. M." box="[286,418,392,414]" pageId="1" pageNumber="230" refId="ref3050" refString="Hilliard, O. M. (1977) Compositae in Natal. University of Natal Press, Pietermaritzburg, 659 pp." type="book" year="1977">Hilliard 1977</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in presenting strongly raised veins below, in lacking underground stolons, and in holding the blades of its much larger leaves more or less horizontal rather than angled.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
